  "texts": [
    "For example, FAO marine fishery data underpins catch reconstructions in the Sea Around Us database 73.",
    "Many limitations of fisheries and aquaculture production data noted above are related to issues with national reporting that are beyond FAO control.",
    "Nevertheless, global fishery and aquaculture data provision can be improved through more detailed metadata, particularly as it relates to data provenance, transparency in assumptions and uncertainty and documenting changes to data through release notes.",
    "Tracing data back to its origins is critical for understanding assumptions in the data collection, detecting errors in the data and linking data with other national data sources.",
    "Thus, relaying the data provenance in the metadata is a critical first step."
  ],
